urls.title: Work continues to support communities across Cheshire following severe flooding – Locally
urls.description: Emergency services and other agencies are continuing to work together to support local communities across Cheshire following persistent rain and severe flooding. Since the major incident was declared on Wednesday 20 January following the arrival of Storm Christoph, agencies have been working around the clock as part of the Cheshire Local Resilience Forum to help ease flood waters, assist people being evacuated from their homes and clear water-logged roads as quickly as possible.
